\section*{Hypothesis Testing for Proportions}


\textbf{Motivation}

\begin{itemize}
  \item We have a claim about a population proportion
  \item We want to test if the claim is true
  \item Obtain data
  \item Test the claim
  \begin{itemize}
    \item Make use of theory from sampling distributions
    \item Use the normal distribution to calculate a p-value
    \item Determine if there is evidence to support our claim based on our data (using the p-value)
  \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\begin{example}
The cracking rate of ingots used in manufacturing airplanes is 20\%. A new process is designed to lower the proportion of cracked ingots. In a random sample of 400 newly designed ingots, 16\% of them are cracked. Is this evidence that the new process actually lowered the proportion of cracked ingots?
\end{example}
