\begin{example}
According to Consumer Reports, 60\% of all U.S. adults like creamy
peanut butter. To investigate this claim, a recent survey polled 675
randomly selected Americans and found that 374 liked creamy peanut
butter. Is this evidence that the proportion of all U.S. adults who like
creamy peanut butter is less than 60\%? (use $\alpha$ = 0.05). 
\end{example}

